## 🔹 Remove Duplicates (Sorted Array)

### 1. Problem
Given a sorted array, remove duplicates in-place such that each element appears only once and return the new length.

### 2. V1 (Brute)
- Use a Set to store unique elements
- Copy back to array

Time: O(n)  
Space: O(n)

### 3. My Stuck
- Initially thought of using extra space (set)
- Didn’t realize sorted property can be used
- Confused about how to overwrite in-place

### 4. V2 (Optimal)
- Use two pointers
- `i` tracks unique position
- `j` traverses array
- If `nums[j] != nums[i]`:
  - increment `i`
  - assign `nums[i] = nums[j]`

### 5. Why is it Better
- Uses sorted property
- No extra space
- In-place modification → O(1) space

### 6. Test
Input: [1,1,2,2,3]  
Output: [1,2,3,_ , _] → length = 3
